text: Okay, so here's the lore as I understand it, since others besides Gura might be a bit confused. Basically, the entity is this transdimensional being that feeds on hope and despair. Each map is actually a pocket dimension created by the entity and the survivors are people who were abducted by it and trapped in these pocket dimensions in order to feed on them by setting them up to attempt to escape. The killers are either past victims of the entity, or people who had been influenced by it to commit horrific acts of murder. Either way, they ended up corrupted by the entity and now live to serve it. The survivors never really escape, they simply leave the map, only for the entity to send them to another one. It feeds on their hope by giving them the illusion of a chance to escape, and on their despair as the killers claim them and they begin to lose hope that they can get out alive.
